**Sec. 60001**
This section rescinds all unobligated balances of funds previously made available to carry out section 132 of the Clean Air Act (42 U.S.C. 7432). These funds were specifically designated for the Clean Heavy-Duty Vehicles program. By rescinding these balances, the government effectively cancels the remaining financial resources allocated for this initiative.

**Sec. 60002**
This section repeals section 134 of the Clean Air Act (42 U.S.C. 7434), which established the Greenhouse Gas Reduction Fund. Additionally, it rescinds all unobligated balances of amounts that were made available to carry out that section prior to the enactment of this Act. This action eliminates both the statutory authority and the remaining funding for the fund.

**Sec. 60003**
This provision rescinds the unobligated balances of funds allocated to carry out section 60104 of Public Law 117-169 (136 Stat. 2067). These funds were intended to support programs focused on diesel emissions reductions. The rescission removes the remaining financial resources available for these specific diesel reduction efforts.

**Sec. 60004**
This section rescinds the unobligated balances of amounts made available to carry out section 60105 of Public Law 117-169 (136 Stat. 2067). These funds were designated for general programs to address air pollution. By rescinding these balances, the Act eliminates the remaining funding for these air pollution mitigation efforts.

**Sec. 60005**
This provision rescinds the unobligated balances of funds made available to carry out section 60106 of Public Law 117-169 (136 Stat. 2069). These funds were specifically allocated to address air pollution at schools. The rescission effectively cancels the remaining financial resources dedicated to this school-based air quality initiative.

**Sec. 60006**
This section rescinds the unobligated balances of amounts made available to carry out section 135 of the Clean Air Act (42 U.S.C. 7435). These funds were designated for the Low Emissions Electricity Program. The rescission removes the remaining financial resources allocated to support this specific electricity program.

**Sec. 60007**
This provision rescinds the unobligated balances of funds made available to carry out section 60108 of Public Law 117-169 (136 Stat. 2070). These funds were intended to support the implementation of section 211(o) of the Clean Air Act. The rescission eliminates the remaining financial resources for this specific regulatory implementation.

**Sec. 60008**
This section rescinds the unobligated balances of amounts made available to carry out section 60109 of Public Law 117-169 (136 Stat. 2071). These funds were designated for the implementation of the American Innovation and Manufacturing Act. The rescission removes the remaining financial resources allocated for this act's implementation.

**Sec. 60009**
This provision rescinds the unobligated balances of funds made available to carry out section 60110 of Public Law 117-169 (136 Stat. 2071). These funds were intended for enforcement technology and public information initiatives. The rescission eliminates the remaining financial resources for these specific enforcement and information programs.

**Sec. 60010**
This section rescinds the unobligated balances of amounts made available to carry out section 60111 of Public Law 117-169 (136 Stat. 2072). These funds were designated for greenhouse gas corporate reporting requirements. The rescission removes the remaining financial resources allocated for this corporate reporting program.

**Sec. 60011**
This provision rescinds the unobligated balances of funds made available to carry out section 60112 of Public Law 117-169 (42 U.S.C. 4321 note; 136 Stat. 2072). These funds were intended for environmental product declaration assistance. The rescission eliminates the remaining financial resources for this assistance program.

**Sec. 60012**
This section rescinds the unobligated balances of amounts made available to carry out subsections (a) and (b) of section 136 of the Clean Air Act (42 U.S.C. 7436). It also amends section 136(g) to extend the program's period from calendar year 2024 to calendar year 2034. While the funding is rescinded, the statutory timeline for the methane emissions and waste reduction incentive program is extended.

**Sec. 60013**
This provision rescinds the unobligated balances of funds made available to carry out section 137 of the Clean Air Act (42 U.S.C. 7437). These funds were designated for greenhouse gas air pollution plans and implementation grants. The rescission removes the remaining financial resources allocated for these plans and grants.

**Sec. 60014**
This section rescinds the unobligated balances of amounts made available to carry out section 60115 of Public Law 117-169 (136 Stat. 2077). These funds were intended for Environmental Protection Agency efficient, accurate, and timely reviews. The rescission eliminates the remaining financial resources for these review processes.

**Sec. 60015**
This provision rescinds the unobligated balances of funds made available to carry out section 60116 of Public Law 117-169 (42 U.S.C. 4321 note; 136 Stat. 2077). These funds were designated for low-embodied carbon labeling for construction materials. The rescission removes the remaining financial resources allocated for this labeling initiative.

**Sec. 60016**
This section rescinds the unobligated balances of amounts made available to carry out section 138 of the Clean Air Act (42 U.S.C. 7438). These funds were intended for environmental and climate justice block grants. The rescission eliminates the remaining financial resources for these specific block grants.

**Sec. 60017**
This provision rescinds the unobligated balances of funds made available to carry out section 60301 of Public Law 117-169 (136 Stat. 2079). These funds were designated for ESA (Endangered Species Act) recovery plans. The rescission removes the remaining financial resources allocated for these recovery plans.

**Sec. 60018**
This section rescinds the unobligated balances of amounts made available to carry out section 60401 of Public Law 117-169 (136 Stat. 2079). These funds were intended for environmental and climate data collection. The rescission eliminates the remaining financial resources for this data collection program.

**Sec. 60019**
This provision rescinds the unobligated balances of funds made available to carry out section 177 of title 23, United States Code. These funds were designated for the Neighborhood Access and Equity Grant Program. The rescission removes the remaining financial resources allocated for this grant program.

**Sec. 60020**
This section rescinds the unobligated balances of amounts made available to carry out section 60502 of Public Law 117-169 (136 Stat. 2083). These funds were intended for Federal building assistance. The rescission eliminates the remaining financial resources for this assistance program.

**Sec. 60021**
This provision rescinds the unobligated balances of funds made available to carry out section 60503 of Public Law 117-169 (136 Stat. 2083). These funds were designated for low-carbon materials for Federal buildings. The rescission removes the remaining financial resources allocated for this materials initiative.

**Sec. 60022**
This section rescinds the unobligated balances of amounts made available to carry out section 60504 of Public Law 117-169 (136 Stat. 2083). These funds were intended for GSA emerging and sustainable technologies. The rescission eliminates the remaining financial resources for this technology program.

**Sec. 60023**
This provision rescinds the unobligated balances of funds made available to carry out section 178 of title 23, United States Code. These funds were designated for environmental review implementation. The rescission removes the remaining financial resources allocated for these implementation efforts.

**Sec. 60024**
This section rescinds the unobligated balances of amounts made available to carry out section 179 of title 23, United States Code. These funds were intended for low-carbon transportation materials grants. The rescission eliminates the remaining financial resources for this grant program.

**Sec. 60025**
This section appropriates $256,657,000 for fiscal year 2025 to the John F. Kennedy Center for the Performing Arts for capital repairs, restoration, maintenance backlog, and security structures. These funds are to remain available until September 30, 2029, and no more than 3 percent may be used for administrative costs. This appropriation is made from any money in the Treasury not otherwise appropriated.

**Sec. 60026**
This section amends the National Environmental Policy Act of 1969 to add a new section 112 regarding project sponsor opt-in fees for environmental reviews. It allows project sponsors to pay a fee equal to 125 percent of the anticipated costs to prepare or supervise the preparation of an environmental assessment or impact statement. In exchange for this fee, the Council on Environmental Quality must complete the environmental assessment within 180 days or the impact statement within one year of the notice of intent. [end of text]


